<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G (Em-centered), 4/4. Hymn opens on Em, cadences on Em.
- LH "33" triads: Em-Bm-Am-D alternation. RH light fifths and thirds.
- Bar 4 dotted rhythm creates breadth at phrase climax.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH common tone B2-B3 maintained through Em and Bm chords.
- RH descends G5→E5 in bar 4 against sustained bass.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Sparse pickup; full bars 1-3; broad bar 4 climax; answering phrase bars 5-7; quiet Em close.
-->
